              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "date": 20030512,
                "history": "U"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Last checking has been done."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target had a thickness of 20% of the interaction",
                "mean free path of the beam particles. This value was",
                "found to be a good compromise to maximize the number",
                "of projectile fragments produced inside the target",
                "without generating too many reinteractions of these",
                "fragments inside the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Track positions on CR-39 foils as well as the track",
                "area and shape of the each figures were determined by",
                "completely automated measurements.They were performed",
                "with scanning system based on computer controlled",
                "microscope stage and image analysis techniques."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " CR-39 plastic nuclear track detectors-",
                "C-12/H-18/O-7. In experiments was used stacks with 3 to",
                "detector foils upstream and 9 to 12 detector foils",
                "downstream a target. Each detector foil had a thickness",
                "of about 640-mum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors. The cross sections are derived from the",
                "number of particles with different charges counted up-",
                "and down-stream the target. Since one has to count the",
                "number of fragments produced inside the target by the",
                "interaction of a well defined number of incoming",
                "particles,the number of projictiles and fragments has",
                "to be counter in congruent areas.  Between 80% and 90%",
                "of all tracks could be reconstructed through the thick",
                "targets. Some  of these tracks were used to determine",
                "the congruent areas on the last foil side in the front",
                "and the first foil side in the back stack."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
